children.name: Strategy & Governance
children.documentation: A layer that defines processes, practices, and organizations (aligned with strategic business planning) to ensure IT alignment and business needs.

children.name: Channels
children.documentation: A layer that must provide products and services uniformly for all channels, enabling multichannel strategy and allowing integration with digital technologies and innovation in offering services to customers.

children.name: Customer Relationship
children.documentation: Layer responsible for the relationship with a whole with the customer, understanding the market and developing new products.

children.name: Products & Services
children.documentation: Products and services that Serasa makes available to the clients.

children.name: Data Management
children.documentation: Layer responsible for data manipulation that will be used for new business analysis and product development

children.name: Operation
children.documentation: Layer responsible for supporting the operations, which includes the functionalities and activities responsible for the management of marketed products. It allows to evaluate the risks of the operation and its degree of conformity to established standards.

children.name: Business Support
children.documentation: Layer responsible for administrative and operational support services
